# language: en

Feature: If-None-Match request-header field
    In order to ignore conditional requests 
    As a exchange developer
    I want to return a normal status for the If-None-Match request-header field

    Scenario Outline: ETag if-none-match request-header field.
        Given I have started a message exchange
        When I perform a HTTP "POST" request to "/queues" with headers "Content-Type: application/json, Accept: application/json, Host: localhost:1984, If-None-Match: "12978507194598101300"":
        """
        " { "data": {                                        "
        "     "name": "acceptance-test"                      "
        "   }                                                "
        " }                                                  "
        """
        Then I should see a response status code of "201" "Created"
        And I should see a "Server" header value "corvusoft/restq"
